A family working through past trauma is not a bad idea for a kids movie, even if it's difficult to tell. It's just that Disney is the wrong studio, as it has a vested interest in showing that the status quo is perfect. The family had no chance of healing, as it *requires* change

Being an AFAB in a family with deep issues, I did a lot of things Mirabel does. Repressing emotions, parentification, overachieving to make up for the lack and get attention - it did some real damage! It only perpetuated the generational trauma in a new way.

The more I think about Encanto, the less I like it. There's a lot to say about the ending, but my biggest beef is that it's telling little girls that they should be responsible for their family's emotional health, manage conflicts, heal generational trauma

I have amazing online friends, don't get me wrong; all of them have been a critical life raft and I love them dearly. Plus the world is on fire in a million different ways. But I can't help but feel regulation problems + unchanging environment have turned my ADHD into a weapon

It's nothing but anecdote, but over the last year my anger problems have only gotten worse, and worry it it's an untreated disorder. But, I've also been living alone in my apartment for almost two years, leaving only once a week. My brain has to be incredibly understimulated

If I'm not paying enough attention (hah), my brain will continue to dump gas on it, and suddenly I am flooded with so much hate and anguish, and I just cannot break away from thinking about it. It's all crisis survival skills, waiting for it to burn out, and keeping isolated

But I'm talking about the anger that flares and consumes everything from the *tiniest* ember. A tweet not even directed at me, something someone said, a tone of voice, my cat being a jerk - it sets me off just a little and then my brain comes in and just dumps gasoline on it

Tbf, lot of anger does come from repeated failure, and the deep frustration of seeing your own inaction with tasks that are critical (lol still haven't paid rent) or important personally (that screenprint I've had since Dec).

I wish there were more articles or *something* about ADHD + emotional dysregulation about the less Tik Tok-able emotions, like anger, anxiety, rage, jealousy. Hyperfocus is a neutral force, and sad to say being in mental anguish is mentally stimulating.

If you want to know how garbage this dev is, check out the censored ending. It's every bit of the dev's garbage ideas about mental health packaged in pretentious garbage. "She's an unreliable narrator so I don't need to write anything cohesive or empathetic, I am very smart"
ONLY NOW does the game pop up with a "hey there's self harm, do you want to censor it?". Go fuck yourself game.

So the next twenty minutes is the character controlling puppets of the mother, Guilia, and Martha, where the game makes you act out scenes of child abuse. Which includes boiling a dog alive and making Guilia eat it. The scene fades to black AND STILL ISN'T FUCKING ENDING
Like Bob says, thanks for making me, the player, do child abuse. Fuck you fuck you fuck you fuck you
https://t.co/hZnIhlUeWw
Oh looook an extra twist Martha died young by her mom's hand actually, but there's still the fetus photo op. It's okay, we're going back to puppet theater to work things out.
But you're spared, and THE GAME IS STILL GOING. I guess there are more shitty twists to put in there in a desperate hope up make the game deep or whatever. Time to listen to a recording of our mom

Finally getting to developing that film and oh what a twiiiiist we killed our sister and our mother! If that's not enough, a soldier busts in and ties Guilia up and we get a grisly torture scene and description because lol you gotta sympathize with the Nazis
@Tabbykit OH MY GOD it's like the worst tweet in the whole damn thread!!

Again, the game got super boring and tedious as fuck, so the dev hits you in the face with more gore. You're running along, with your mother's head in your hands the entire time like it were a lantern.

As the player you spend the next fifteen minutes playing with puppets, recreating what really happened (because the game will allow no other interpretation), and it turns out Guilia murdered and dismembered her mother. The puppet show ends and you're holding your mother's head

We're heading to dipshit takes on mental health town, hoooooray! Btw the place is getting bombed now I guess?? But we're off to the room to hell the White Lady story again, but this time with puppets! It's no less facile than in the beginning, but puppets!

Okay so she gets back, and a weird vision shows us she's waiting to capture us and take us to the asylum. Guilia tries to sneak in and is caught, and then shoots her mother dead. She's like "It's not me who did this!" and finds the keys to her locked happy room on the mom
Then we set the fetus on her heart and took a real nice photo. Two tweets ago it was the dullest shit, then this was dropped in. The writer/developer is an idiot, a hack, and a coward.

Swastika banners around our sister's coffin in the mausoleum.

...somehow that's the least offensive thing that will happen in here, as we cut open our dead sister's stomach with a pair of scissors, rummage around, and pull out a deformed fetus to use as proof of pregnancy

What this game is like to play

https://t.co/5bhYvdebYo

So the game still isn't over, and now we're trying to find more evidence about the murder. Also everyone knows it's Martha that died, but nothing has changed. This game has the tension of a stick of string cheese.

The game did a huge reveal that Martha was never deaf, and she was just pretending, which their mom blamed on Guilia. Also she was pregnant, so that's why we had a phantom miscarriage because sure. What a twist?

One intensely long slog and terrible puzzle, we do a ritual to summon to the White Lady and ask her if our mom murdered Martha. The White Lady was at the beginning, but you summon her in the daytime and it's just fine? The tone is just all over the place and unintelligible

So... Why? Was it to push the plot forward? Just to get in some more gritty points with abuse? This is a game that will literally spell out a metaphor in excruciating detail, but the plot is so threadbare and nonsense.

Soooo after the funeral, Guilia started playing the piano and was caught by her mom, so now everyone knows she isn't Martha. Did the dev just write themselves into a corner?? They were super quick to follow that reveal up with physical abuse and threats to send her to an asylum

"My father hates this war, which is why he's a GENERAL in the SS.

I want medication to be affordable to everyone; ADHD meds have dramatically improved so many lives. On good days they were a lifesaver! I just also want us to live in a world that doesn't require us to break ourselves to survive.

I put this on the timeline not only because I'm a chronic oversharer, but to emphasize that MANY people make this decision in the name of surviving in this capitalist hell system. There are no options, you have to be functioning at a job to eat/live and damn everything else.

I can layer ADHD meds, SSRIs, and mood stabilizers to be a semi functional wreck, but a few months ago I was in a terrible place. Bad med mix, bad life events, and extended pandemic isolation combined put me in a state of such paranoia, anger, and sadness. (Good support sys tho)

Putting the implications of that medication interaction aside, I now have to decide on a bit of productivity or emotional stability, because there are no more options*. 

*That insurance will cover lol great system I love it

Been off my ADHD meds for about a month now, and have come to the sorrowful conclusion that the meds give me a bit of focus and make it easier chain thoughts together at the incredibly high price of dumping gasoline on already heightened emotions and vulnerability

If no one gives a shit, you don't have to give a shit either! And if they give up on you, well, you were right all along. You don't have to try, you just get to be always right and fucking miserable. And what a fucking spit in the eye of people who *do give a shit about you*

Used to have a friend that proudly proclaimed that "No one gives a shit about you", as if this fact freed you from the expectations and hurts of others. Tonight I finally nailed down what pisses me off about it.

It's nothing but emotional cowardice.
Every horror movie featuring dogs is always a little undercut by knowing those acting dogs are having the time of their lives
But I'm going to let them go, to let someone else enjoy them! Make space for new memories, including the one where I only need one shipping cube lmao

Anyone with ADHD has a huge pile of things and hobbies they were into deeply at one point, and then lost interest. It feels terrible, and like a shameful waste; you hold onto everything "just in case", but it only covers joyous memories in terrible thorns.

Since I know I'm moving many months from now instead of having three weeks, I'm starting to go through the whole place a closet at a time and really Kondo-ing the place. This time I'm working very hard to give away or forgive myself for half finished or failed projects

"Is this actually what I think? If my body does not align with my thoughts, which one is the correct one?" Like people with a severed corpus callosum, a fractured person operating in tandem with itself, but unknowing of itself.

You see all of the things you desperately want, and the many paths to get them! But you don't move. Two people in one body, and they don't speak the same language. The lack of follow through on anything is so pervasive, you begin to doubt yourself and your very thoughts

I've been on so many medications, tried so many different styles of therapy, but the disconnect is deep and unyielding. The worst part is it being inconsistent - strategies that work one week, don't work the next.

The worst part of this mental health *gestures vaguely* situation is the deep incongruence between the body and mind. Some days things sync up and I can get stuff done and my outlook is better. Other days I struggle to shower and just stare at my coffee without drinking it
